Chelsea fullback Ola Aina says he’s enjoying his loan at Torino. Aina is expected to start for this weekend’s clash with Napoli. He said, “The city of Turin? I like it. It is smaller than London and quieter. READ ALSO Lagos SWAN salutes Pinnick, others “It suits me. The player I’m inspired by? Marcelo of Real Madrid. But when I was little, I really liked David Beckham. “My role? I started playing as a winger, then over the years I have stepped back. This position allows me to attack, but also to defend: I always try to do what the coach asks me. “Next match? Sunday we face Napoli and it will be a very difficult game.” 